    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_8e9e887b-94e6-426a-af61-967c9853f1ab" class="text-block-content">
    <p>If you have added a non-scoring rubric to an assignment, you can assess the rubric in SpeedGrader. Non-scoring rubrics contain rating criterions without point values. Unlike regular rubrics, non-scoring rubrics are not used for grading.</p>
<p>Be sure you have selected the <strong>Remove points from rubric</strong> option when <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-add-a-rubric-to-an-assignment/ta-p/1058" target="_blank">adding a rubric to an assignment</a>. <em>Be sure this checkbox is selected before you begin grading submissions</em>.</p>
<p><strong>Note</strong>: If your rubric does not contain any predetermined rubric criteria, you should grade the rubric using <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-use-free-form-comments-instead-of-ratings-in-a-rubric/ta-p/1011" target="_blank">free-form comments</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open-speedgrader" data-step-uuid="989f2c75-7d45-4ea8-831e-2b2abd8fc49e">
    <h2 id="open-speedgrader" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open SpeedGrader</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/001/735/625/original/618aad0e-f6db-4075-9746-26d2c38b8af8.png" srcset="" alt="Open SpeedGrader" height="54" width="170">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_b196ab14-2a5d-4214-951e-7409e70f1f1e" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Open SpeedGrader from any assignment, graded discussion, or quiz.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open-student-submission" data-step-uuid="fd874bee-6d92-4d7d-a8e6-109addcbcf66">
